The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, August 02, 2004  Calcutta Column
				 																																									A massive anti-plastic campaign was undertaken in the city recently to spread awareness about the hazards of using bags and cups made of plastic of thin variety. However, most shops in Gariahat do not stock paper cups. I had a get-together at home and had to buy plastic cups.				 																																									Sekhar Basu Mallik, 				 																																									Ashabori Apts.				 																																									The Lake Town post office took a month to hand me my original National Savings Certificates (NSC). This affected submission of my tax returns. The proposal in this years budget of authorising banks to sell NSC should be implemented to ensure better service to people.				 																																									Rabindranath Kar,				 																																									Sankar Ghosh Lane.
